# Div render (layout builder)

Read `.cursor/AGENTS.md` and `skills/generate-div-json/SKILL.md` before generating div JSON.

## JSON rules

- Required: `type: "div"`, `id`.
- `children`: `LayoutBuilderItem[]` — nested items (default `[]`).
- `className`: primary way to express layout (flex, grid, gap, spacing).
- `style`: inline CSS object when needed.
- HTML div attributes allowed (except `children`): `role`, `aria-*`, `data-*`, `id`, `tabIndex`, etc.
- Legacy `props` nested object merged onto DOM (prefer top-level attrs for new JSON).
- Designer-only: dashed outline when `path` is set (not in production JSON concern).

## Layout patterns

- Row of buttons: `className: "flex gap-2 justify-end"`.
- Page section: `className: "space-y-4"`.
- Grid: `className: "grid gap-4 md:grid-cols-2"`.

## Pitfalls

- Using div for clickable actions — prefer `button` type.
- Missing `children` key — omit or use `[]`; nested items go in `children`.
